cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with object recognition using depth information. It also involves deep learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a novel deep architecture. Additionally, it involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it uses prior knowledge to sparsify feature maps. The paper also deals with robotics (cs.RO) as object recognition is an important task in robotics. Finally, it involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it proposes a new weight update method for training the network.
